caption:
This photograph provides an aerial view of a lush, forested landscape intersected by a straight, paved road. This main road stretches vertically through the image, bisected near the center by another road that runs horizontally, forming a clear crossroads. The surrounding area is dense with various shades of green, dominated largely by tall coniferous trees, which suggest a forested or rural region.

Adjacent to the roads, small clusters of residential houses can be seen. These houses, appearing as small white and gray specks, are surrounded by open land or yards, and are relatively sparse compared to urban settings. There appear to be no high-rise buildings, indicating a likely suburban or countryside setting.

In addition to the houses, there are hints of agricultural activities; neat rows that could possibly be crops or a small orchard are visible on the right side of the photograph. Clearings in the forest nearby might be used for similar purposes, or perhaps they serve other community functions.

Overall, the area captured in this image represents a tranquil setting where human habitation merges minimally with the natural forest environment, maintaining a balance between development and nature. The presence and arrangement of the roads suggest functionality and accessibility in this serene locale.
title: Aerial view of the Central Valley quadrangle which is bounded by Tracyton, Illahee, Brownsville and Silverdale. These communities and others in the area will be affected by population growth when the navy's proposed Trident submarine base is built nearby.
